<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Belgian actress Annie Cordy has died at the age of 92.</p>

<p>The acclaimed screen star passed away following a cardiac arrest at her home in Vallauris, France.</p>

<p>Annie was known for starring in an array of French films after making her debut in 1954, and was made a Baroness in 2004 in recognition of her achievements.</p>

<p>RIP: Belgian actress Annie Cordy has died at the age of 92 after suffering a cardiac arrest at her home in Vallauris, France</p>

<p>It's been reported by The Mirror that attempts were made to revive Annie after she suffered a cardiac arrest, but she was pronounced dead.</p>

<p>The screen star had been living in France with her niece.</p>

<p>French television host Christophe Beaugrand-Gerin paid tribute to Annie in a moving tweet, which translated to read: 'I'm heartbroken tonight. Mrs. Annie Cordy, you have given us so much joy, energy and emotions. We won't forget you.'</p>

<p>Iconic: Annie was known for starring in an array of French films after making her debut in 1954, and was made a Baroness in 2004 in recognition of her achievements</p>

<p>Annie's last on-screen appearance came in the 2018 film Illiterate, and by that point she had appeared in more than 50 films and TV series.</p>

<p>Among her most iconic roles were Royal Affairs in Versailles in 1954, and The Singer from Mexico in 1956.</p>

<p>She even voiced Grandma Willow in the country's translation of the 1995 Disney animation Pocahantas.</p>

<p>Amazing: Annie - real name Leonie, Baroness Cooreman also boasted a successful singing career with numerous performances at the Paris Olympia in France (pictured in 1987)</p>

<p>Annie - real name Leonie, Baroness Cooreman, was born in Belgium in 1928, and also boasted a successful singing career with numerous performances at the Paris Olympia in France. </p>

<p>She also topped the French charts for six weeks in 1956 with her ballad La Ballade de Davy Crockett.</p>

<p>After decades of success Annie was made a Baroness by King Albert II of Belgium in 2004, and a Commander of the Order of the Crown in 2013.</p>

<p>Throwback: Her last big screen role came in the 2018 film Illiterate, and by that point she had appeared in more than 50 films and TV series (pictured in July 2018)</p>
